tion": "Area: SIMD (Single Instruction Multiple Data)"}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2021-04-09T20:16:27Z", "updated_at": "2021-07-21T20:37:05Z", "closed_at": "2021-07-21T20:37:05Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When playing around with x86_64 SIMD intrinsics, I found that `_mm_loadu_si64`, which loads 64-bit value into 128-bit vector register, work incorrectly compared to intel's intrinsic guide. According to guide, value should be put in lower half of register. Intrinsic puts it into upper half.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse core::arch::x86_64::*;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let v = u64::to_le_bytes(0x0123456789abcdef);\r\n    // according to intel's intrinsic guide, value should be loaded into lower half\r\n    let m64 = unsafe { _mm_loadu_si64(v.as_ptr() as _) };\r\n    eprintln!(\"m64: {:#x?}\", m64);\r\n\r\n    let l = unsafe { _mm_extract_epi16(m64, 0) };\r\n    eprintln!(\"l: {:#x?}\", l); // should print `0xcdef`\r\n    let h = unsafe { _mm_extract_epi16(m64, 15) };\r\n    eprintln!(\"h: {:#x?}\", h); // should print `0x0`\r\n\r\n    let v = u128::to_le_bytes(0x0123456789abcdef);\r\n    let m128 = unsafe { _mm_loadu_si128(v.as_ptr() as _) };\r\n    // should be the same as `m64`\r\n    eprintln!(\"m128: {:#x?}\", m128);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n[Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=99d78bb276fd62de433d35b20ef7fced)\r\n\r\nLooking at [implementation of `_mm_loadu_si64`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.51.0/src/core/up/up/stdarch/crates/core_arch/src/x86/sse.rs.html#1248-1250):\r\n\r\n```rust\r\npub unsafe fn _mm_loadu_si64(mem_addr: *const u8) -> __m128i {\r\n    transmute(i64x2(0, ptr::read_unaligned(mem_addr as *const i64)))\r\n}\r\n```\r\nit looks like `0` and `read_unaligned` are swapped (as x86 is little endian, lower half comes first).", "closed_by": {"login": "Shadlock0133", "id": 3766527, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM3NjY1Mjc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3766527?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133", "html_url": "https://github.com/Shadlock0133", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Shadlock0133/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84042/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/84042/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}